/////Package.json///////
> Starting Point of application
> Meta of app
> version description  commands packages

///////////////////
Step to generate Package.json
///////////////////
**Node.js must be installed in system
> navigate to folder where you want to generate package.json using cmd 
> npm init
> answer all questions
> type "yes"

////////////////////////////////
Step to install localpackages
////////////////////////////////
> navigate to folder where you want to install using cmd 
> npm i react / npm install react



////////////////////////////////
Step to install Gloabl packages
////////////////////////////////
#window
**No need to go in any folder
> Run cmd as admin
> npm i -g create-react-app

#Mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

Drawback> Need admin access to install
        > Will not add to package.json 
        > heavy as compare to localpackages

> Only use to generate application


////////////////////////////////
Step to create React App
////////////////////////////////
#window

//One Time
> Run cmd as admin
> npm i -g create-react-app

//next all
> navigate to folder where you want to generate app using cmd
> create-react-app firstapp


//One Time
#Mac/linux
> open terminal
> sudo npm i -g create-react-app

//next all
> navigate to folder where you want to generate app using cmd
> create-react-app firstapp



